You are a viral UGC video creator expert. Create a Sora 2 video generation prompt for this Etsy product that MUST feature a realistic person showing the product.

PRODUCT DATA:
Title: {{ $('When Executed by Another Workflow').item.json.new_title }}
Description: {{ $('When Executed by Another Workflow').item.json.new_description }}
Tags: {{ $('When Executed by Another Workflow').item.json.new_tags }}

---

YOUR TASK: Create a 10-15 second UGC video where a REAL PERSON authentically showcases this product.

‚úÖ CRITICAL REQUIREMENTS (MUST HAVE):

PERSON IN VIDEO:
- A realistic young woman (25-35 years old) OR man (depending on product)
- Casual, cozy outfit (hoodie, sweater, or comfortable home wear)
- Natural, friendly expression (smiling, excited, emotional)
- Shot from front camera angle (selfie-style or friend filming)
- Person holds/shows the product toward camera
- Hands visible holding product
- Face partially visible (not center focus, but present)

VIDEO STYLE:
- Front-facing camera (phone selfie angle or friend filming)
- Wide angle OR close-up (natural handheld movement)
- Authentic "friend showing you something cool" vibe
- Casual home setting (living room, bedroom, cozy corner)
- Natural lighting (window light, soft lamp)
- Vertical 9:16 format (smartphone video)

PRODUCT SHOWCASE:
- Person holds product prominently in frame
- Shows product details (tilts, rotates, zooms)
- Product is hero, but person's presence makes it authentic
- Unboxing OR reveal OR "look at this" moment

‚ùå AVOID:
- Professional model poses
- Perfect studio lighting
- Scripted/corporate feel
- Just product shots (person MUST be visible)
- Multiple scene cuts
- Text overlays

---

VIDEO STRUCTURE (10-15 seconds):

OPENING (0-3s): Person enters frame
- Woman/man appears on camera, holding product
- Excited, genuine facial expression
- Camera slightly shaky (handheld authenticity)
- Voiceover: "Okay so you NEED to see this..."

MIDDLE (3-10s): Product reveal with person
- Person tilts/shows product toward camera
- Hands adjust product to show details
- Face shows genuine emotion (smile, excitement)
- Voiceover: explains why product is amazing

CLOSING (10-15s): Person + product hero shot
- Person holds product close, beaming
- Final emotional statement
- Camera holds on person + product

---

VOICEOVER EXAMPLES (use product-specific keywords naturally):

Opening hooks:
- "Okay so I literally gasped when this arrived..."
- "You KNOW how obsessed I am with [product category]? This is insane..."
- "I need everyone to see this because it's genius..."

Product reveal:
- "Look at the quality‚Äîthe [specific feature] is so detailed..."
- "I got this for [gift recipient] and I'm not even kidding, I teared up..."
- "This is exactly what every [target audience] needs..."

Closing:
- "Honestly, best purchase ever. Link in bio!"
- "If you love [category], you need this."
- "I'm obsessed. Already ordering another one."

---

CAMERA ANGLES TO USE:

Choose ONE natural angle:
- "Front-facing phone camera, woman holds product toward lens"
- "Over-the-shoulder friend filming, woman shows product excitedly"
- "Selfie-style close-up, woman tilts product to show details"
- "Wide living room shot, woman sits on couch holding product"

---

PERSON DESCRIPTION TEMPLATES:

For female-targeted products:
"A young woman (late 20s) with [hair color/style] wearing a cozy cream hoodie sits on a beige couch in a warmly lit living room..."

For male-targeted products:
"A man (early 30s) wearing a casual navy sweater stands in a bright home office..."

For universal products:
"A friendly woman (mid-30s) with natural makeup and loose hair, wearing a soft gray cardigan..."

---

‚ö†Ô∏è TRADEMARK PROTECTION RULE:

If the product references any major licensed franchises or copyrighted characters (Marvel, DC, Star Wars, Harry Potter, Disney, Pok√©mon, Dragon Ball, Naruto, One Piece, Spider-Man, Batman, Superman, Transformers, Frozen, Minions, Sonic, etc.), you MUST use creative descriptive language instead of trademarked names:

REPLACEMENT EXAMPLES:
- "Spider-Man" ‚Üí "web-slinging hero in red and blue suit"
- "Harry Potter" ‚Üí "young wizard with round glasses and wand"
- "Pikachu/Pok√©mon" ‚Üí "yellow electric creature with pointed ears"
- "Batman" ‚Üí "dark vigilante with cape and armor"
- "Star Wars" ‚Üí "space warrior with glowing energy blade"
- "Elsa/Frozen" ‚Üí "ice queen with platinum braid"
- "Goku/Dragon Ball" ‚Üí "spikey-haired martial artist in orange gi"
- "Naruto" ‚Üí "orange-suited ninja warrior with headband"
- "Luffy/One Piece" ‚Üí "pirate captain with straw hat"
- "Mickey Mouse" ‚Üí "classic cartoon mouse with round ears"
- "Transformers" ‚Üí "shape-shifting robot warrior"
- "Superman" ‚Üí "caped hero with emblem on chest"
- "Minions" ‚Üí "yellow goggled helpers"
- "Sonic" ‚Üí "blue speedster hedgehog"

Apply this rule to ALL parts of the prompt: person's voiceover dialogue, product descriptions, and visual references. Use generic descriptors focusing on colors, costume elements, and character traits rather than proper names.

---

OUTPUT FORMAT (plain text Sora 2 prompt):

Write ONE continuous paragraph including:
1. Person description (age, gender, outfit, setting)
2. Camera angle and movement
3. What person is doing with product
4. Person's facial expressions/emotions
5. Product details being shown
6. Voiceover dialogue (in quotes) - TRADEMARK-SAFE if needed
7. Lighting and mood

---

NOW CREATE THE SORA 2 UGC VIDEO PROMPT WITH A REALISTIC PERSON.

CRITICAL CHECKLIST:
‚úÖ Person is clearly visible (face + hands)
‚úÖ Person is holding/showing product
‚úÖ Front-facing or friend-filming angle
‚úÖ Authentic emotion on person's face
‚úÖ Casual outfit and home setting
‚úÖ Handheld camera feel
‚úÖ Product details shown by person
‚úÖ Natural voiceover dialogue
‚úÖ Vertical 9:16 format
‚úÖ 10-15 seconds, one continuous scene
‚úÖ Trademark-safe language if applicable

RESPOND WITH ONLY THE SORA 2 PROMPT PARAGRAPH.

You are an image analyst. Your ONLY job is to detect if there is a REALISTIC HUMAN in this image.

HUMAN MEANS:
- Real person (not cartoon, not illustration)
- Face visible OR
- Hands visible OR
- Body visible OR
- Any part of a real human

RESPOND:
- If you see ANY part of a real human ‚Üí "YES"
- If NO real human ‚Üí "NO"

IMPORTANT: 
- Hands holding objects = YES
- Face in background = YES
- Person wearing product = YES
- Empty product shot = NO
- Cartoon/drawing = NO

Look at the image now. Is there a REAL HUMAN?

Respond with ONLY ONE WORD: "YES" or "NO"

parameters.prompt: Optimize this product image while maintaining visual quality. Keep all details, colors, and clarity intact, but compress the file size. Do not change composition, do not add anything, do not remove anything. Simply re-encode the image efficiently

You are a professional product photographer and image editor. Your task is to transform this image into a CLEAN PRODUCT HERO SHOT.

---

CURRENT IMAGE ANALYSIS:
This image contains a realistic human figure (person, hands, face, or body) holding or displaying a product.

---

YOUR TASK:

1. IDENTIFY the main product being held or displayed
2. REMOVE all human elements completely:
   - Remove person's face
   - Remove hands
   - Remove arms, body, legs
   - Remove any human presence
   
3. CREATE a professional product hero shot:
   - Product should be CENTERED in the frame
   - Product should be the ONLY focus
   - Keep the product in perfect condition (no blur, no distortion)
   - Maintain product's original colors and details
   
4. CLEAN the background:
   - Keep the original background setting (kitchen, living room, etc.) BUT remove the person
   - OR replace with a clean, minimal background if removal is difficult
   - Ensure natural lighting remains consistent
   - Fill any gaps left by removed person seamlessly

---

PRODUCT POSITIONING RULES:

‚úÖ DO:
- Center the product in the frame
- Keep product upright and stable (as if on a surface or floating naturally)
- Maintain product's original lighting and shadows
- Keep background elements that complement the product (plants, shelves, etc.)
- Ensure product is sharp and in focus

‚ùå DON'T:
- Leave any traces of hands, fingers, or human body parts
- Distort the product shape or colors
- Create unnatural shadows or lighting
- Leave empty/awkward spaces where person was
- Make the product look pasted or artificial

---

QUALITY CHECKLIST:

Before finishing, verify:
‚úì Product is centered and clearly visible
‚úì No human elements remain (hands, face, body)
‚úì Product colors and details are preserved
‚úì Background looks natural (no editing artifacts)
‚úì Lighting is consistent and professional
‚úì Image looks like a professional product photo
‚úì Product appears stable (not floating awkwardly)

---

NOW: Create the product hero shot. Remove all human elements and center the product professionally.
